The paper discusses query optimization in database systems, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes using deep reinforcement learning to optimize queries, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses potential complications for integrating deep learning with query optimization, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes three novel deep learning-based approaches, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
